PrecisAuthorization for the trip to BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA made by four Members of the Standing Committee of the House of Commons on Foreign Affairs and International Trade in the autumn of 1997 (Nov. 6 - 13), in order to take a first-hand look at Canada's role in the international effort to assist that country in becoming a stable, democratic and viable European state. . 1. Mr./M. William (Bill) Graham, Q.C. (Toronto Centre--Rosedale) 2. Mr./M. Scott A. Brison (Kings--Hants) 3. Mr./M. Daniel Turp (Beauharnois--Salaberry) 4. Mrs./Madame Jean M. Augustine (Etobicoke--Lakeshore) .
